data/parameters.yaml-154-
data/parameters.yaml-155-# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/parameters.yaml:156:# TWO ORTHOGONAL ADJUSTMENTS (GiveWell-style), kept deliberately separate:
data/parameters.yaml-157-#
data/parameters.yaml-158-#   causal_credibility (per archetype, below) — IS THE MEASURED EFFECT REAL?
data/parameters.yaml-159-#     Internal validity only: how well the study design identifies causation.
data/parameters.yaml:160:#   realization_factor (global, here) — DOES SCOTT'S DOLLAR DELIVER IT?
data/parameters.yaml-161-#     Everything between a real effect and her marginal grant: external
data/parameters.yaml-162-#     validity/transport to her grantees, overhead leakage, counterfactual
data/parameters.yaml:163:#     funging — net of the capacity benefits of large unrestricted gifts.
data/parameters.yaml-164-#
data/parameters.yaml-165-# Division of labor: transportability concerns live HERE, not in credibility;
data/parameters.yaml-166-# cost-per-QALY priors are conditional on the effect being real and delivered.
data/parameters.yaml-167-# Each doubt enters exactly one layer.
data/parameters.yaml-168-#
data/parameters.yaml-169-# LIMITATIONS (disclosed, not hidden): credibility is drawn independently per
data/parameters.yaml:170:# archetype, while realization is one global draw — two opposite correlation
data/parameters.yaml-171-# extremes. A tier-correlated credibility variant widens the 90% interval ~7%
data/parameters.yaml-172-# and leaves the median unchanged. Credibility is also strictly positive, so
data/parameters.yaml-173-# the model puts no mass on zero or harmful effects; for assumption-tier
data/parameters.yaml-174-# buckets the mean of 0.07 approximates, but never reaches, a null.
data/parameters.yaml-175-# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/parameters.yaml:176:realization_factor:
data/parameters.yaml-177-  dist: triangular
data/parameters.yaml-178-  low: 0.55
data/parameters.yaml-179-  mode: 0.80
data/parameters.yaml-180-  high: 1.10
--
data/parameters.yaml-182-  source: >-
data/parameters.yaml-183-    AI-PROPOSED, AUTHOR-REVIEWED PRIOR (no literature estimate exists for this quantity).
data/parameters.yaml-184-    Downweight for transport/overhead/funging; upweight allowed past 1.0
data/parameters.yaml-185-    because [Center for Effective Philanthropy (2023)](https://cep.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/BigGiftsStudy_Report_Y2_FNL.pdf)
data/parameters.yaml:186:    finds large unrestricted gifts materially expand recipient capacity/reach.
data/parameters.yaml:187:    Stress-test with the interactive's realization slider (it moves the MODE of
data/parameters.yaml-188-    this triangle within [0.55, 1.10]).
data/parameters.yaml-189-
data/parameters.yaml-190-# Evidence tiers by causal-identification design. AI-PROPOSED, AUTHOR-REVIEWED
data/parameters.yaml-191-# PRIORS (Claude drafted the levels):
--
data/parameters.yaml-195-# AND a wider distribution. No published calibration of design -> credibility
data/parameters.yaml-196-# exists; the ordering is the defensible part, the levels are judgment.
data/parameters.yaml-197-evidence_tiers:
data/parameters.yaml-198-  randomized:     {mean: 0.85, concentration: 22, design: "RCT / clean natural randomization (e.g., lottery)"}
data/parameters.yaml:199:  strong_quasi:   {mean: 0.65, concentration: 13, design: "Credible quasi-experiment (DD/IV) with admin data and checks"}
data/parameters.yaml-200-  moderate_quasi: {mean: 0.45, concentration: 8,  design: "Quasi-experiment with notable concerns or a contested literature"}
data/parameters.yaml-201-  observational:  {mean: 0.22, concentration: 6,  design: "Associational; confounding-prone"}
data/parameters.yaml-202-  projection:     {mean: 0.15, concentration: 6,  design: "Model/IAM projection; no direct causal estimate for this lever"}
data/parameters.yaml-203-  assumption:     {mean: 0.07, concentration: 9,  design: "No causal health evidence; skeptical expert prior"}
--
