361:What are marginal funding and marginal impact?
362-
363:Marginal funding is the last funding that goes to a program. It’s
364:important because the impact of marginal funding is often different from
365:the average impact of funding to a program.
366-
367:For example, imagine that the Against Malaria Foundation is considering
368:funding the distribution of insecticide-treated nets in Nigeria. They
369-have identified two areas as excellent candidates for distribution:
370-
371:- They could distribute $1 million worth of nets in areas with the
372-  highest rates of malaria. This would save 200 lives at the cost of
373:  $5,000 per life saved.
374:- They could distribute an additional $2 million worth of nets in areas
375-  with lower rates of malaria. There is less malaria to prevent, so it
376-  costs a bit more to save lives. This distribution will save 250 lives
377:  at the cost of $8,000 per life saved.
378-
379-The average cost to save a life with this program if fully funded with
380:$3 million would be about $6,700 per life saved.
