paper/review/round1/neutrality.md:17:7. MINOR — §4.2 "plausibly under 20–40×... under any plausible account": speculative universals; "the honest statement" implies alternatives dishonest. Fix: tie to the cited GiveWell floor; "the defensible statement is directional... under the diminishing-returns accounts in the cited literature."
paper/review/round1/methodology.md:9:   **Problem:** The code does literally apply each of the two explicit multipliers once: \(Q_{ij}=D S_{ij}R_i C_{ij}/K_{ij}\). That establishes absence of a duplicated line of code, not the stronger claim that “each doubt enters exactly one layer.” Several cost-per-QALY priors already mix concerns assigned elsewhere. The cash prior spans adult RCT null results and positive child quasi-experiments and is then assigned a `strong_quasi` credibility multiplier; the education range is anchored to a contested literature including null findings and is then discounted again as `moderate_quasi`; and the global-health prior blends program types and GiveWell-style modeled effectiveness before receiving both credibility and realization multipliers. Conversely, the model omits harmful effects and does not propagate uncertainty about the tier means. Calling realization a “discount” is also imprecise because it can reach 1.10. The intended partition is sensible, but it is not presently demonstrated parameter by parameter and may both double-count and omit uncertainty.  
paper/review/round1/methodology.md:24:   **Problem:** The stance endpoint is mislabeled and one substantive attribution is wrong. At stance 0, the code leaves the randomized-tier mean at 0.85 and sets every other tier to 0.01, not zero; it therefore represents “default credit for the randomized tier plus a small positive floor elsewhere,” not restriction to randomized evidence. In the reproduced run, the endpoint has median 9,114 QALYs and mean 13,090; the largest mean contribution is 8,806 QALYs from the randomized collaborative-care mental-health bucket. It is not “dominated by the one lottery-randomized bucket”: the cash bucket containing the lottery evidence is classified `strong_quasi` and is pushed to the 0.01 floor. At stance 1 all tier means are 0.999, not exactly one. The piecewise-linear path also has a kink at 0.5 and, because concentration is held fixed, changes Beta variances mechanically as means approach zero or one. Calling this arbitrary scenario path an “honest bound” is too strong.  
