56-Social Investing
57-
58-At Constellation, we treat every philanthropic dollar like an
59:investment. The returns we measure are lifetime improvements in the
60-actual health and earnings of our neighbors struggling with poverty.
61-
62:This year, our portfolio achieved a record benefit-cost ratio (BCR) of
63-$8.54. In plain terms, that means for every dollar donated through
64-Constellation, we estimate roughly $8.54 in measurable income and health
65:benefits flowing to participants. Those benefits start materializing
66:fast — it takes only 15 months to flip to a positive social return on
67:investment. Our portfolio generated an estimated $33.9 million in total
68:impact in 2025, and our grantees impacted more than 250,000 people in
69-the Twin Cities who experience measurable improvements in their lives.
