75-What’s remarkable is the trajectory. When we started in 2021, our
76:benefit-cost ratio was $5.03. It has grown consistently each year to
77-where it is today. That reflects our team’s ongoing refinement of how we
78-evaluate organizations and how we allocate capital — concentrating
79:dollars where the evidence shows the strongest returns.
80-
81-Consider one of our grantees as an example: American Indian OIC. Their
82-Takoda Institute offers career training that leads to
83-industry-recognized credentials — in phlebotomy, commercial driving,
84-tech support, and more. When a participant earns one of those
85-credentials, it opens the door to higher wages that compound over years.
86:That’s the kind of growth our benefit-cost ratio captures: real, lasting
87-economic mobility for people in our community.
