102-These examples aren’t outliers. They represent exactly what our model is
103-designed to find: organizations executing efficiently, backed by strong
104-evidence, and creating the most measurable value per dollar for
105:participants. And not only does our portfolio deliver a great return but
106-it does so with remarkable stability. Each donated dollar through
107-Constellation is roughly three times more risk-efficient than a dollar
108-given without this kind of rigorous impact data.
109-
110-Of course, we’re working hard to continue to improve how and what we
111-measure. Some critical areas — housing in particular — are genuinely
112:hard to measure. Housing benefits accrue over decades, and they’re
113-correlated with many other factors, meaning isolating the impact is a
114-challenge. Fortunately, CoLab, Constellation’s research-funding arm, is
115-investing in the kind of longitudinal research that can fill in those
116-gaps. Constellation is committed to following the evidence, even when it
117-takes time to develop.
